inn1.comm: played towards square leg for a single, Watson's away immediately
played towards cover, no single on offer this time
played off the front foot towards midwicket
pushed off the front foot firmly towards cover
square driven off the front foot to the point boundary
played off the back foot towards midwicket for a single
slides it wide down the leg side
gets half forward and pushes it to mid-off
this one moves away and beats the outside edge
he slashes at one pitched up and the ball flies off the outside edge wide of slip and down to third man
gets beside the line and steers it to point
stays back and softly pushes it to the off side
length ball, defended on the back foot
fuller, snaking towards off, thick edge down to third man
leaps off a length, taking a chunk of the top edge, flying about half way to third man
on the stumps, nudged to mid-on
length, room outside off, hacked down the ground
yorker on the stumps, Watson jams his bat down on it
too wide from Bravo and the batsman cuts hard past the diving man at cover
on the legs this time and nudged away for a single

is this out? Bravo thinks it should be lbw and West Indies have asked for a referral ... The ball seamed back at Watson, inside his expansive drive, flicking the front pad before running through. It's very close but just appears to strike Watson outside the line - and the review is turned down.

another big appeal, this time for caught behind! The ball moved a long way back from outside off - a terrific delivery - and Baugh took a diving catch down the leg side. Appeared to have flicked the pad rather than the bat, though.
squirted away to deep backward square
pitched up, knocked out towards cover
on leg-stump, tickled fine of the hips for a couple to Watson
full, on the stumps and driven wristily through midwicket
length, Warner steps away and slashes a brutal cut shot through extra-cover, the ball motoring away to the rope
again room for Warner to cut but he can't force this one past cover-point
slanted across the left-hander, played out to point
drops a tad short, on leg, and forced away to the square boundary
length, nudged into the leg side
turn for Narine, spinning in and popping off Watson's pads to short leg
on the stumps, bit of turn, tickles Watson's glove before deflecting off his pad to fine leg
tossed up outside off and Warner lets it through
outside leg and turning, beats Warner's outside edge - beautiful delivery
tossed up and played back on to the wicket
West Indies have their breakthrough! Watson took on the fielder at mid-on but couldn't beat Andre Russell's arm, a direct hit sending him on his away about two inches short
short, pushed to cover
back of a length, hacked back down the ground
full, right up in the blockhole, Warner gets his bat down on it
pitched up again, glanced away to square leg
length ball, pacy, slices through Wade as he attempts a dab outside off
outside leg, not much turn, thumps into the pad as Warner pushes forward
tossed up more and spinning hard, misses with a wild hook
on the stumps, nudged to midwicket
flighted outside off, Wade shuffles across and defends on the front foot
nearly another run out! Wade, crab-like moves across and ticks Narine toshort leg - he stuttered after setting off and would have been out to a direct hit at the other end
turning from outside leg, beats Warner's prod
well-directed short ball from Roach thunders into Wade's chest
length, angled across, inside-edged past the stumps to long leg
pitched up, punched to mid-on
full, drives hard but straight to cover
maintains full length, driven to extra cover - can't find a way through again
almost yorker-length, Warner brings his bat down on it
outside leg, turning across, pushed into the off side
around the wicket, defended in front of the stumps
back around, prodded back by Wade
beaten outside off by one that spits and turns
tossed up on the stumps, defended

Got him! Wade has been shuffling across, shuffling across - and now he's been bowled round his legs! Narine got enough turn to bring the ball back between Wade's attempted glance and his pad, the ball clattering into middle and leg
on the legs, turned away to deep backward square
full, driven out towards cover
length ball, Bailey goes back and turns it to leg
full, on the stumps, squirted away square
sticks in the pitch and Warner loops the checked drive short of mid-off
fuller, chopped into the ground and through to the keeper
outside off, turning in, played back down the wicket
a tad short and Bailey pulls past square leg
beautiful line from Narine, luring Warner forward and beating his outside edge as he tries to drive through the off side
tossed up and left as it turns away
drags slightly short, cut hard but well fielded at point
the doosra from Narine, cuts Warner in half as he opened his arms, the ball flying over the stumps and past Baugh
shortish, defended into the off side
full, straight, knocked down to mid-on
strays on to the pads and clipped to deep backward square leg
outside off, keeps low and jabbed to short midwicket
back of a length, anlged across and Warner doesn't quite connect with an airy pull, the ball doing just enough to clear the man running back towards deep midwicket
driven from outside off through cover
flighted, not quite so much turn, deflecting off Baugh's gloves after Warner left
on leg, played with the spin to point
flatter, turning across the left-hander, patted out towards the point boundary
tossed up outside off and pushed to cover
flatter and quicker, beating Bailey's pull stroke and hitting him on the pads, outside off
flighted, Bailey comes forward and defends tentatively
edged through the vacant slip region - Australia's first boundary in almost ten overs

this time the edge finds a man and Warner is gone! He leaned into a cover drive but the ball didn't quite reach him as quickly as he expected, Warner stretching and the ball flying off the toe to the safe hands of Pollard at point
pitched up, driven back to the bowler
length, dropped short to cover and Hussey has to dive to make his ground after calling for a quick single
outside off, pushed into the covers
tighter line and screwing away off bat and pad towards extra-cover - Bailey still seems unable to time his shots properly
length, pushed square on the off side
pitched up outside off, swinging away a little, Hussey declines a shot - perhaps could have been called a wide
length, on the stumps, defended coming forward
again offering Hussey width, angled across the left-hander, but left alone
good line and length, the batsman steps out and lets it go by
width and Hussey goes for it this time but his cut is athletically saved by Pollard at point
length, outside off, pushed to cover
pitched up and driven through the gap
line and length outside off, nudged to cover-point
on the stumps, slightly shorter and pulled round the corner to long leg
angled across from leg, pulled fiercely square by Hussey but rescued on the boundary by Russell
length ball outside off, drawing the batsman forward to play and miss
good length and straight, played towards point from the crease
fuller ball angling across the left-hander, driven towards point on the front foot
length ball outside off, Hussey has width and he cuts between backward point and short third man
he comes forward this time and drives to cover
short of a length around off stump, defended on the back foot
fuller length outside off, Hussey strides forward and drives to cover
too full and too straight, Hussey gets on to the front foot and turns the ball off his pads past short fine leg
a full toss, Hussey was forward too early and played it to mid-off, it was a slower full toss
good length and straight, Hussey defends on the off side and Sammy runs across to field
played from the crease to point
Hussey drops the ball with soft hands close on the off side and runs a quick single, Pollard rushes in from point and tries to kick the ball on to the stumps
played close on the off for another very quick single, Pollard is unable to prevent it and he kicks the air
good length on off stump, Bailey defends on the front foot
full ball angling into middle stump, flicked towards midwicket
good length around off stump, defended from the crease to the off side
a length ball outside off, quite driveable that was and Bailey freed his arms to hit through cover
good length on middle and off, defended from the crease behind point
Hussey chases a length ball as it angles across him and gets beaten on the cover drive
good length and straight, Bailey stays in his crease and dabs towards point
defended on the off side
fuller length on a straighter line, turned off the pads behind square
good length and straight at 145 kph, Hussey gets behind the line and blocks
Hussey moves forward and pushes a good length ball towards long-off
speaking of Samuels, he's in the way of a firmly-hit cover drive and does well to block it. Hussey came forward and hit the full ball hard towards cover
full and straight, Baily moves forward and drives firmly into the ground, Bravo sticks his left hand out and deflects the ball wide of mid-off, Bailey sees an opportunity and runs a sharp single
played back to the bowler from the crease
driven off the front foot towards the off side
Hussey has width again outside off and he cuts hard, this time there's a fielder at third man
short of a length outside off, hit hard off the back foot towards cover
full on middle and leg, clipped off the pads towards long-on
length ball outside off, played from the crease towards point
Bailey slogs across the line at a good length ball and gets beaten, that was close to off stump
turned off the pads towards fine leg
Hussey moves forward and plays the ball close on the off side
driven uppishly but past the diving fielder at cover. Bailey moved forward and drove that on the up, hitting through the line

there's a direct hit at the bowler's end but the batsman is safe. Pollard hesitated for a long while before throwing and so Bailey's dive saved him. Hussey had pushed towards point and Bailey ran a long way down from the non-striker's end before turning back
played off the back foot in front of point
defended on the front foot, that ball hit the pad so Samuels appealed but it had pitched outside leg, only just
Hussey tries to drive but is beaten outside off as the ball spins across him
defended on the off side
played on the off once again
shorter length and Bailey uses the spin into him to pull behind square
Bailey moves across his crease and flicks towards deep square leg
Hussey steps out of his crease and defends on the leg side
a slow full toss, Hussey moves forward and drives to mid-off
Bailey presses forward and defends one that angles into him towards cover
short of a length and straight, played off the back foot towards midwicket, the throw to the keeper is sloppy and there's an overthrow
a front-foot no-ball, which Bailey drives towards long-on, Hussey will have a free-hit to attack
and he's put it to good use, Hussey clears his front foot, waits for the slower ball and pulls it past the fielder at midwicket and into the gap on the boundary
Bailey gets down on one knee and sweeps towards long leg
pitches outside leg and spins across the batsman, Hussey moves back and taps behind square
played off the back foot on the off side

edged off the back foot but the ball falls short of slip, Hussey went deep into his crease and was squared up by one that pitched outside leg and spun across him, he took his bottom hand off the bat and the ball fell short of Dwayne Bravo
played off the pads behind square
defended on the front foot
good length angling into the right hander, played towards midwicket
Bailey stays in his crease and flicks towards midwicket again
short of a length, Bailey glances off his hips through square
a short ball, and Hussey lets it go over him
played through midwicket for a single, the ball was full and slower than the previous one
played through square leg
defended from the crease on the leg side
Bailey moves outside off, gets down on one knee, and sweeps to deep square leg
Narine pitches on a good length, drawing Hussey forward, and then spins it past the outside edge of his forward defence
this time Hussey goes right back to defend, and gets beaten outside off once again
Hussey slog sweeps and places the ball wide of the fielder at short third man, towards deep backward square leg
Bailey moves back in his crease and gets squared up while defending
good length and straight, defended back to the bowler
Hussey takes two steps out of his crease but has to defend in the end, the length wasn't there to hit
a slower and shorter ball, Hussey stays on the back foot and pulls
short of a length around off, Bailey pulls towards deep square leg
played close on the off side for a single, Bravo is quick to the ball from point but then takes a while to decide which end to throw at, he goes for the non-striker's and misses
pulled gently behind square for a single
Bailey goes back to play on the leg side but gets hit high on the thigh
Bailey pushes forward to defend but doesn't manage to very convincingly
quicker and straighter, Bailey defends on the front foot
a tough too short, allowing Bailey to wait on the back foot and pull to deep square leg
Hussey's destroyed Narine's economy of just over one per over here, he got down on one knee and swept powerfully over the deep midwicket boundary, very clean hit
left alone outside off as the ball spins across him
played off the front foot towards long-on for a single
short of a length outside off, hit of the back foot towards cover
Bailey moves across his crease and turns the ball off his pads towards fine leg
good length around off, Hussey defends from his crease on the off side
defended on the front foot towards cover point
driven off the pads towards long-on for a single
Hussey goes back and tries to hit the short ball through cover as it spins across him, he finds the fielder
defended on the back foot on the off side
steered off the back foot to point
Hussey moves forward and blocks
driven on the front foot to long off
Bailey stays in his crease and defends on the leg side, Samuels ambles across to defend
Hussey pushes towards mid-on and runs
Bailey moves back and defends a good length ball towards the bowler
Bailey muscles a pull in front of the fielder at midwicket, he jumped out of his crease and then had to wait for the ball
Hussey tries to hit the ball a bit too hard but mis-times the shot
a full slow ball, Hussey steps out and taps to midwicket for a single, Samuels throws needlessly at the non-striker's end and hits the stumps, they run an overthrow for the rebound
pulled towards deep square leg for a single
played towards Pollard at midwicket
full ball outside off, driven on the front foot towards long-on

Hussey's top edged a sweep but the ball falls safely at deep square leg, Hussey wanted a second run but Bailey did not. Hussey turned back after running a long way down but luckily for him the throw was to the keeper's end
played to deep square leg
cut hard off the back foot towards point
pushed into the gap at cover point for a quick single
pitched up, driven to long-off
length, outside off, pushed towards cover - "No!" yelps Bailey
full, on off but whipped through midwicket
outside leg, pushed through midwicket
very full but straying on to leg stump and squeezed out sharply to the backward square boundary
length, defended on the back foot into the on side
tossed up, quick singled nudged out to point
flatter, on the stumps, flipped towards square leg
pitched outside off but spun a long way down leg
give some air and played very late by Bailey, steering it past the keeper and down to third man, where the fielder gives chase
tossed up, turning and beating the bat outside off
on the stumps and driven to long-off
flighted, swept over the infield, bouncing once before finding long leg
full, driven back and fielded by the bowler
loses his line down the leg side, flicking the pad before skidding to the fine-leg boundary
pitched up, punched to cover
length, squirted through point on the walk
Hussey also uses his feet, narrowing the gap between himself and the bowler and steering Roach through cover-point
fulll delivery, driven to long-off
on the stumps, defended
drops short, swivels quickly into position and pulls to square leg
short, pushed off the back foot to point - there's a chance of a run out but the trhow's not good
dragged short, missed with an attempted guided outside off
flat, turned towards square leg
length, outside off, steered behind point
big lbw shout - it hit Bailey in line but was perhaps a shade too high. Bravo holds his head in his hands
beats the outside edge with one that skids across Hussey outside off
nudged  away through cover - and that's Hussey's fifty. Mr Cricket is probably enjoying this
turned to leg off te stumps and that's a half-century to Bailey too - his first in international cricket
room outside off, deflected to short third man
pitched up, driven down the ground to long-on
full, driven through extra-cover and the batsmen hustle back for a second run
full again, nurdled to midwicket
steps out and carts a big six over long-on - that was an effortless slog from Bailey
flat, on the stumps, tries to turn to leg but the ball squirts back to Samuels
swings hard on the pull - but he's sent it straight into the hands of square leg! It was a clean connection but unfortunately for Bailey he picked out Dwayne Bravo, who coolly pockets the ball
length, flicked to the man at short midwicket
tight line, on the stumps, worked into the on side
pitched up, driven to the fielder at cover
length ball, room outside off, steered to third man
straight long-hop and David Hussey seizes on it to whips a muscular hook shot out to the vacant deep midwicket boundary
length, nudged into the leg side
room outside off, the batsman leans into a drive past cover - they think about two but quickly reasses
flat, worked to midwicket
flighted a bit more, slight turn, inside-edged towards square leg
tossed up and swept hard to deep square leg
on the stumps, bit of bounce, worked square on the leg side
drops shorter, turned to midwicket
outside off, punched to the cover fielder
length, slanted across the lefty, driven on the up wide of mid-off
rank ball, short and down the leg side, battered round the corner to long leg
pitched up a bit more, on the legs, Michael Hussey skips out and punches through midwicket
targeting the body, batsman gets on top of it and drops te ball to midwicket
room outside off, driven to long-off
length, guided down to third man
flighted, guided from outside off round the corner behind square
tossed up, Mike Hussey reverses his grip and shovels a sweep - but straight to third man
flatter, spinning across and Hussey misses with a swipe
full, flicked off the pads for a hard-running couple to deep midwicket
tossd up outside off, turning further - too far
strays on to the pads and Hussey again finds the gap through midwicket
on the stumps, defended on the front foot into the off side
full, David Hussey tries to glance but gets a leading edge over the head of point
drops short as Hussey advances, missing with an attempted glide outside off
pitched up, driven to midwicket who fields smartly and has a shy at the non-striker's end
length, worked out to deep backward point
length ball, outside off, the batsman plays and misses
touch short, David Hussey tries to hook but can't get it off the square
drags it short, pulled through square leg for one
length ball, the batsman dances out and lofts the ball high over midwicket, coming to earth just in front of the rope before kicking on
flatter, nurdled into the leg side
got him! Cannily done by Samuels, dragging his length down as Hussey advanced, getting a bit of bounce past the bat and leaving Hussey stranded. Baugh does the handiwork
length, outside off, spinning in and Christian can't get anything on it
on the stumps, turned to midwicket

Another one goes - a fabulous slower ball from Roach castles the younger Hussey! The batsman backed away, aiming for a swipe down the ground, but Roach rolled his fingers over it, the ball dying as it reached the crease before spinning into middle stump, half way up
bouncer, way over Lee's head - welcome to the crease

two in the over! Lee plays on! Roach sent down another slower ball, this not as well-directed, but the pace did for Lee who was through his windy drive too quickly, getting a thick bottom edge on to the timbers
steered into the leg side
back of a length, prodded to point, well-fielded
Christian is beaten for pace outside off, his loose drive nowhere near connecting
full, worked off the pads into a gap at midwicket
on off, flicked over his shoulder for a couple to fine leg
doesn't pick the wrong-un and Christian is hit on the arm trying to slog-sweep
another doosra, outside-edged to point

McKay falls to the doosra! Australia are floundering like Andrew Flintoff in a pedalo! The batsman played back uncertainly and got a thin nick on one that went away from him. Looked like it might have clipped off, if he hadn't snicked it. That's four wickets for six runs in 13 balls
tossed up, spinning hard and beating Doherty's prod outside off
beaten outside off by another doosra

Darren Bravo shows footballing skills Dwight Yorke would be proud of to run out Doherty! Christian dropped it short on the off side, Bravo hared in and side-footed the ball into the stumps from about six yards. GOOOOOAL!
strays on to the legs and Lyon gets a sliver on it, the ball scooting fine to the rope
full, poked into the off side
length, outside off and pushed to cover
back of a length, Lyon stays in the crease and is beaten as he dangles his bat out
fuller, wide of off and the batsman steps out for an ostentatious leave
full, chipped over the infield and Pollard kicks the ball in from the deep midwicket boundary
dragged down as Christian advances, drilled back to the bowler
this time he connects! That's huge six - though he was nowhere near the pitch. He simply stood and smoked it over long-on
beaten trying to heave through the leg side by another wrong'un

Christian is given out lbw - but he calls for the review. It hit the batsman full on the toe, in front of leg stump. Christian was hoping it was sliding down leg ... but it didn't have far to go and the replays suggest the ball would have thunked into the stump. He has to walk and West Indies have rounded up the last six wickets for 18 runs

inn2.comm: nice flowing start, the batsman eases on to the front foot and drives a length ball from outside off through cover
length ball on middle and leg, Charles tries to glance behind square but misses and gets hit high on the pad
good length and straight, Charles defends from his crease to the bowler
full ball on middle and leg, Charles once again doesn't connect with the flick
played from the crease off the pads behind square
short of a length outside off at 132 kph, Powell stays in his crease and defends on the off side

he wasn't playing a shot there was he? McKay angled the ball down leg side and Charles tried to let it go, the ball hit his left thigh and raced towards fine leg, where the fielder dived to save the boundary. He needn't have bothered, the umpire called dead ball
once again he misses the leg glance and gets hit high on the pad
played towards midwicket for a quick single
short of a length on the pads, Powell plays from his crease towards square leg
McKay appeals for lbw but that pitched outside leg, Powell tried to flick but missed and was hit on the pad
Powell moves across his crease and defends a straight ball
that's not too short but Charles manages to play a controlled pull shot, swatting it from his crease to the backward square leg boundary, kept it along the ground
defended on the off side from the crease
played off the back foot towards point
Charles is through his pull far too early and gets hit on the shoulder, that was the slower short ball from Lee, rolled his fingers over it as he released it
a quicker ball outside off, Charles pushes forward and gets beaten
played in front of square leg for a single
good length around off stump, defended back towards the bowler
full and straight, Charles drives but the fielder at mid-on runs to his left to cut it off
the ball keeps low and nips in from a good length outside off, beating Charles between bat and body
that's a loose drive on the front foot at a good length delivery which holds its line after pitching outside off, he gets beaten
Charles has another swish at one outside off without moving his feet, makes no contact
this time he moves forward and towards the off to drive a length ball on the up towards point, doesn't beat the field though
Powell tries to drive straight but mis-times it on the off side
that's only slightly short and Powell leans towards the off and pulls between midwicket and square leg, he hit that against the angle across him from over the wicket
superb timing, Charles opened the face of the bat and used Lee's pace to steer the ball behind point, it raced to the boundary beating third man, who was running to his right
fuller and straighter, played with a close face towards midwicket
driven on the front foot through cover
that's a bit too wide outside off
played off the pads behind square
Powell goes back and blocks
defended from the crease on the leg side
full delivery angling into the stumps, driven towards mid-on
steered off the back foot towards point
wicket to wicket line once again, the batsman defends
slightly short in length outside off, cut off the back foot to point
drifts into the right-hander, pitches on leg and middle, and begins to turn towards off, Charles moves forward and blocks
Powell comes out of his crease and drives firmly to short midwicket
Powell goes back to a fuller and straighter ball and is beaten outside off stump
shot! Powell goes down the pitch, didn't get to the pitch of the ball but still hoisted it off his pads over the midwicket boundary

he's been stumped now! He came down the track again, once again didn't get to the pitch of the ball, and was beaten by the straighter one. He pushed forward to try and defend but was beaten as the ball skidded past his outside edge. Wade whipped off the bails with the batsman well short
full and straight, Charles plays to midwicket
that's only a bit short and Charles slogs the ball from outside off to the deep midwicket boundary, he had to time it well to have beaten Michael Hussey
this time it's behind square on the off side. Charles playing the square drive, reaching away from his body to steer a length ball behind point, timing it beautifully
defended from the crease on the leg side
good length and straight, Charles defends from his crease
that's been blazed through point, too full from Lee and Charles played the square drive perfectly on the front foot, moving forward and swinging his bat hard
Samuels pushes from his crease and gets beaten by the ball as it rips across him, big turn

huge appeal for lbw, Kumar Dharmasena says not out and Australia want the decision reviewed. Doherty strikes Samuels full on the boot as he defends from the crease so the umpire has to assume the ball is going straight on, with the angle of the arm, it would have missed leg stump
left alone outside off stump
quicker ball fired into the pads, Samuels misses the glance
defended on the front foot towards point
strides forward once again to defend
the short of a length ball climbs on Charles, who drops his wrists and lets it go after having a little fend at it
good length and straight, Charles gets behind the line and defends
that's a loose shot, Charles simply swung at it without moving his feet, the fuller ball on a good length outside off took the inside edge and went past leg stump and the keeper
played off the back foot with an open face towards third man
played towards point on the off side, Samuels pushed half forward and defended that
steered from the crease towards third man
defended on the front foot
Samuels moves forward and outside the line of off stump to defend but gets hit on the pad by the offbreak that turns quite a lot
defended on the front foot and he makes contact this time
steps out of his crease and hits the ball hard through midwicket
gets down on one knee and sweeps through square
defended on the front foot
good length and straight, Charles moves forward to defend and gets an inside edge on to the pad
good length on off stump once again, defended on the front foot towards the bowler
defended back towards Watson once again from the crease
Charles steps out of his crease and mis-times the pull to midwicket
defended off the back foot with an open face towards point
he does play this pull shot so well, Charles leans back and rolls his arms to keep the ball along the ground towards the deep backward square leg boundary
defended on the front foot, Samuels got a good stride in to smother the spin
this time he gets hit on the pad as he tries to defend but it was outside the line of off stump
defended on the front foot towards the leg side
Samuels moves forward and outside the line of off stump while defending
played off the front foot towards point
pitches outside off and spins into the right-hander, hitting the pad as Samuels pushes forward, Lyon appeals but lots of doubt about that one
Charles stays back and plays the ball towards square leg

that looks plumb lbw and the umpire agrees. Samuels is on his way, he's decided not to review. Watson pitched full and straight, Samuels defended from his crease, as he usually does. He missed and was hit around the knee roll on the back pad. Absolutely plumb. That held its line instead of angling into the right-hander
defended on the front foot towards the off side
full and wide outside off, driven on the front foot towards point

a soft dismissal, Watson pitched the slower ball on a good length outside off, angling across the left-hander. Bravo came forward and tried to drive on the up. He ended up spooning it straight to the fielder at short cover who caught it at head height
good length angling towards leg stump, played off the pads towards midwicket
defended on the back foot on the off side, that spun a long way into the right-hander
Charles gets down on one knee and tries to sweep, misses and is hit on the pad
defended back to the bowler

that is a colossal hit into the stands beyond long-off, Charles came down the track, wasn't to the pitch of the ball, but still swung hard, freeing his arms. He made good contact and timed it beautifully
swept behind square for a single
played through point and there's a mix-up as they attempt the second, all's well in the end for West Indies
full ball angling into the right-hander, played towards midwicket
defended from the crease towards the off side
good length outside off, driven towards mid off for a single
Watson induces an inside edge towards fine leg, Bravo wanted to flick that squarer
a full ball swings into the right-hander and hits the pad after Charles misses the flick, Watson begins to appeal but realises it was missing leg
played towards point where Michael Hussey is quick to prevent the single

how has that carried for six? Bravo backed away to an offbreak that spun sharply into him from outside off stump and punched into the air over extra cover. It looked like he had hit it straight up but evidently he hadn't, it cleared the extra-cover boundary easily
that's spun down leg side
played off the pads behind square
defended on the front foot
Charles tries to sweep but doesn't make proper contact
quicker and flatter ball, defended from the crease
strides forward to defend outside off stump
full, straight and Charles gets his feet out the way and drives down the ground to the bowler

skips forward again - and gone! Charles lofts an innocuous delivery from Watson straight to cover. Australia's captain has a golden arm, doesn't he? And that ends Charles' innings five short of what would have been a maiden international fifty
full, straight, defended back to the bowler
pitched up, Pollard gropes outside off stump but is beaten
tempting length, seaming a touch and Pollard props forward and misses outside off
straighter line, Pollard gets behind this one and defends into the off side
spits one out of the rough! That turned a mile, from around off to well outside, almost beating Wade
flighted, tip and run to cover
tossed up, on leg stump and edged square ... and there's almost another mix up, Pollard sent back by Bravo after he had advanced half a dozen yards
full length, pushed towards cover
full, on the stumps, Pollard leans around his pads and defends
tossed up on leg and chipped to mid-on - Bravo is sent back this time, in a muddle of arms and legs as the throw comes in
full, driven to mid-off
length, room outside off and driven square, fielded at backward point
pitched up and timed sweetly off his pads through midwicket
defended into the off side on the front foot
keeper up the stumps ... defended on off, pushing forward
length, Pollard gets solidly behind it and pushes into the covers
tossed up on off, spinning sharply away from the batsman, who plays no stroke
pushed into the covers for a scrambled single
flighted, on off and defended on the front foot
flighted, on leg stump and tickled into the leg side
tossed up and defended on the stumps
another one is bitten by the dust! Bravo tried a back-foot force but got a thin edge through to Wade, who clung on well. The slow bowlers are in their element on this dry strip
full, worked off his pads for a quick couple
full, driven away square on the off side
back of a length, cut hard but fielded by backward point
length delivery, steered behind point
full, straight and clipped to deep backward square again
bouncer, which Pollard concertinas his considerable height under
tossed up by Doherty and he gets big turned outside off, Baugh planting his foot but keeping his bat out of the way
lured forward on off stump and Baugh is beaten past his outside edge
flighted, on the stumps and Baugh gets his bat behind this one on the front foot
pitching on off and turning, hits Baugh on the pads - but the appeal is turned down
tossed across towards leg, straightening and again striking the pad
full, Baugh gets forward and squirts the ball out to point - that's a maiden for XD
full and quick from Lee, the batsman gets behind it
pitched up on the stumps and worked towards midwicket, cut off by the fielder
length ball outside off and Pollard steps out, swings hard through midwicket - it wasn't the cleanest connection but there was still enough power to get it to the rope
yorker length but Pollard gets his bat down on it in time
full toss and BOOMED out of the ground! Pollard set his shoulders and swung straight through the line, sending the ball whistling back over Lee's head - and over the roof of the stand at long-on
touch shorter, on the stumps and worked square off the legs
flighted, outside off and dabbed to short third man
shorter, flatter, Pollard tries to hack through the off side and inside-edges past his stumps
beaten by one that turns past the outside edge and there's an appeal for a stumping - but Pollard had got his foot back
floated up outside off and Pollard guides it past the fielder inside the circle
on the stumps, drifting down leg and deflected via Baugh's pad, though it struck him outside the line
on the legs and Pollard flicks it round the corner for two
length, outside off and dabbed down to third man
not enough pace to trouble Pollard, who pushes to cover
decent length, room outside off for Baugh to punch square again
on the stumps and worked into the on side
keeps up that nagging line, propped square but too close to the fielder
dropped short on the off side and they snatch a single - though a direct hit would have run Pollard out
drops short and Pollard steps back, loosens his arms and swings like a lumberjack, the ball rollicking away to the cover boundary
goes back and plays a more delicate stroke to third man
big appeal again from Doherty, the ball thunking into the pad as Baugh pushed forward - again there was a question about the line of off stump
swung hard from outside off to deep square leg on the sweep
tossed up and played back to the bowler
outside off and clipped to point
off-stump line, knocked into the covers
drops slightly short, Baugh tries to hook but the bounce deceives him and he wears the ball on his body
back ot a length again, plopped out to cover
pitched up and driven square, slight misfield at point
straighter, on the stumps and flicked off the hips in front of long leg
slower ball from McKay, pitched up outside off and Baugh jams his bat on it
flat delivery, quickish, prodded into the off side by the big man
pitched up and Pollard steams another big six down the ground, swinging his arms gaily
room outside off to cut but Pollard can't beat the man at point

goes big ... but this time he can't clear the rope. Pollard is gone! He went for another maximum but didn't quite hit through the ball this time, picking out Lyon's spin twin Doherty on the boundary. DK has jinxed his man ...
straighter line, pops up off the pitch and loops past short leg off a pad
floated up outside off and scuffed to a fielder on the drive
pitched up outside off and left by the batsman
full, outside off and Russell clears his front foot to swing a clean, forceful drive over mid-off and away to the fence
straighter, dropped into the off side

hello, goodbye! Russell picks up McKay's slower ball and deposits it on to the roof of the stand. Not sure it went quite as far as Pollard's but it was still an almighty heave. Looks like they'll need a replacement ball, too ...
angled into the body and dabbed towards short midwicket
length and beats the stroke, swinging down the leg side
tossed up and dribbled into the leg side
length, spins back, chopped to point
tossed up, outside off, spinning into the pad
dragged wider and Baugh misses with a lusty drive
played out to point, against the spin
flatter, outside off and spinning back - again hit on the pad but the appeal is half-hearted. Maiden from Lyon
short, whipped away to backward square leg
back of a length again and Russell hammers it over cover, the fielder getting a finger tip to it but only serving to take the pace off
length, flicked through cover as the batsman comes forward
flicked off the pads through square leg
short, angling in and thrashed baseball-style down the ground to long-on
length ball, played into the off side
tossed up, beating Russell's inside edge to hit the pad - umpire shakes his head
flighted in, striking the pads again but well outside off
tossed up and driven hard through cover to the rope
drags his line across and paddled around the corner this time
turned off the legs into the on side
shorter, outside off and spinning back, hitting the batsman on the body
short of a length around off stump, Baugh defends from his crease
fuller length but the line is down leg side
Baugh gets down on one knee and swings a length ball towards fine leg
Russel begins to make room by moving towards leg but then defends to the bowler
pushed off the back foot towards midwicket and they run a single before the fielder on the edge of the circle can come running in
played off the front foot to cover
good length and straight, Baugh stays back and dabs towards point and a sharp single
big turn into the right-hander, he's moved towards leg and dabbed that from outside leg stump towards short third man, that bounced high as well
Russell attempts a slog sweep but gets an inside edge on to the pad
he's pulled that flat and hard towards deep midwicket where Lee sprints to his right and taps the ball back into play in the nick of time
pushes forward to defend but gets an outside edge past the keeper for runs
defended on the back foot towards the off side

Russell strides forward and plays the cover drive with immense power into the gap on the boundary, he hit it all along the ground too. Lyon had flighted that ball outside off stump, but Russell hit it against the turn.
good length and straight, Baugh stays in his crease, gets behind the line, and defends tentatively ...
shorter length angling into the body, Baugh fends towards square
length ball wide outside off stump, Russell reaches for it and throws his bat at the ball but can't make contact
steered from the crease towards point where the fielder runs and dives to his right to save runs
defended back to the bowler
driven off the front foot towards cover, Watson bowls a maiden with the field in the circle
Baugh strides forward and outside the line of off stump to defend but gets hit on the pad

what's he trying there? Baugh backs away, exposing all three stumps, and tries to slog inside out over the off side as the ball turns away from him. He gets beaten and would have been bowled had the ball not turned so much past off stump
Baugh gets hit on the pad and the ball lobs to slip, there's an appeal for a catch
defended on the front foot to the bowler
played off the back foot towards point with an open face
he's fired that down leg side and Wade yelps in pain because that ball's smacked him on the knee cap
defended on the leg side, no runs off the bat in the first two batting Powerplay overs
pushed off the front foot towards the bowler
good length and straight, defended from the crease to cover
good length on middle, that ball straightened off the pitch and Russell defended it from his crease
defended towards midwicket once again, no width at all from Watson, wicket to wicket on a  good length
relentless line and length, Russell tries to work towards square but gets a leading edge towards the bowler
Russell tries to drive but gets an inside edge on to his shoe and towards the off side, Watson fields
defended on the front foot on the off side
finally, Baugh goes back and cuts the ball as it spins away from the right-hander, the ball is pulled in close to the third man boundary, Warner was chasing it
beaten outside the off stump
defended towards cover
Baugh slog sweeps, and gets a top edge over the keeper's head
Baugh tries to slog, his front leg planted outside leg stump and his bat flailing wildly in the air, he gets beaten by the turn away from him

Watson's 150th wicket is likely to be a game-breaking one. The pressure tells on Russell, he backs away and slogs at a good length and straight ball. He misses and Watson hits the stumps. Russell begins to walk off but then waits, the umpire wants to check if Watson has over stepped. He has! Huge break for West Indies. Russell can bat on.

he's bowled him again! But Russell can't be out because it's a free-hit. Russell tried to pull a good length ball and missed once again. I haven't seen that happen. Bowled twice in a row but not out both times
Baugh tries to play the big drive but gets an inside edge on to the pad
defended on the off side
Watson pitches full outside off and nips the ball in, Baugh stays in his crease and tries to cut, he gets beaten
short of a length and straight, played towards square
good length and straight, pushed towards long-on for a single
the ball rises on Russell from short of a length and he tries to pull off the front foot, the top edge lobs safely towards midwicket
Baugh's found the boundary! He had width to cut and he made good contact and placed it into the gap on the third man boundary
Baugh drives loosely away from his body and is beaten by the slower ball
he's found the boundary again! This time off the outside edge. Baugh swung hard at a length ball outside off, he was aiming for long-off, he found the third-man boundary instead
the very slow ball outside off stump but the line is too wide
defended on the back foot, the line was wicket to wicket from McKay
a slow full ball, it looped towards the blockhole and Baugh drove trough cover
played from the crease towards point

Lee appeals for lbw because the short of a length ball doesn't rise that much and hits Baugh on the thigh after he misses the pull, that looked high though, replays indicate it might have clipped the bails
flicked off the pads towards midwicket
good length on off, Russell pushes at it from his crease and gets an outside edge towards third man
a full ball wide outside off, Baugh is beaten but Wade fumbles, allowing the bye
good length outside off, Russell taps in front of point and sprints to retain strike
Russell wanted to send that to the midwicket boundary but toe ended the ball past the diving Wade towards third man, he was too early on the pull
Baugh moves across and turns the ball to short fine leg, Russell steams through for the single. Things are beginning to happen ...
caught behind! Russell tries to cut, the ball was slower outside off and he got a thick edge which Wade caught by diving to his right, McKay roars in celebration.
wide outside off stump, cut towards third man
on the pads, clipped to short fine for single
good length and straight, defended on the front foot

Baugh moves towards the off and hooks a short of a length ball awkwardly towards fine leg, Doherty sprints after it from short fine leg and slides in the nick of time to save four, Wade had also run after it and he fired the throw in
beaten outside off stump
pushed towards point for a single
good length and straight, defended to the bowler
good length outside off stump, defended towards the bowler again
Sammy gets squared up in his crease as he defends a good length ball towards the off side
played from the crease towards cover
driven from the crease towards backward point
Baugh wafts outside off and gets beaten
shot! Baugh moves towards the off and swings a length ball from middle and leg to the deep backward square leg boundary, fine leg was in the circle. Top shot

he's been caught now! McKay pitched the slower ball delivered from the back of the hand on a good length, Baugh swung hard and across the line, hitting the ball high towards midwicket, where Christian held the catch
Sammy moves forward and drives to cover for a single, keeping the new batsman Narine off strike
Lee roars an appeal for lbw after he hits Sammy just above the pad, looked a little high, Wade runs to his right to limit the leg byes
played off the back foot on the off side
defended from the crease towards cover
the short of a length delivery climbs on and angles into Narine from round the wicket, Narine does well to let it go
Narine tries to drive the fuller ball through cover but mis-times it towards the bowler
played from the crease towards point
good length and very straight, Sammy gets behind the line and defends to the bowler
the line is a bit straighter, Sammy chips the flick flat over the infield at midwicket
Watson goes round the wicket to Narine and beats him outside off stump
too full on the pads, clipped through midwicket and even the fleet-footed Michael Hussey on the midwicket boundary can't prevent the second
Watson's line is poor again, on the pads, Narine stays balanced and closes his face to turn the ball behind square and into the gap on the boundary
Narine's playing a gem for West Indies. He stays extremely balanced on the front foot and launchs a length ball from outside off to the wide long-off boundary
short of a length outside off, Sammy pushes to point for a single and the crowd is cheering everything now

splendid catch at short cover! David Hussey throws the ball in the air in celebration. Length delivery angling into the right-hander from round the wicket, Narine drove at it and hit the ball on the up, he middled it but the ball went straight to Hussey who took a low catch
full ball outside off, driven to cover
short ball outside off stump, Roach lets it go
Lee's bowled the full ball wide down leg side, Wade collects
Roach takes on McKay's arm from third man and beats the throw comfortably, he had steered it with an open face
a full ball outside off, Roach plays the square drive to deep point and runs the single, so Sammy will not have the strike

that's fired down leg side and Roach sweeps, I think he got some bat on that and the ball races towards fine leg. The fielder slides to prevent the ball from hitting the rope but his foot was touching the rope, that's a boundary. West Indies need 9 off 11 balls. Australia need one wicket
Roach chases a wide ball outside off and gets beaten
swept toward fine leg for one more, there's tremendous noise at Arnos Vale at the moment
Sammy pushes the ball to cover and sprints, there's a direct hit but Roach is safe at the striker's end, the umpire asks for replays to be doubly sure
defended back to the bowler
played with an open face behind point
Sammy slogs at a full ball around off and forces it towards midwicket, Watson dives at extra cover to prevent the overthrow
Roach jumps back and opens the face to steer a short of a length ball towards third man, sensible batting from the No. 11
Sammy's tied the scores with a fearsome hit, thrashing the ball flat towards the wide long-on boundary. The fielder at long-on ran to his right and dived desperately, he couldn't stop it

Oh Roach, what have you done? After batting with such composure, with West Indies on the verge of victory, Roach sets off for a non-existent single after Sammy had played the ball towards point. Actually Sammy had begun to run as well and then stopped, looking in desperation as Roach continued towards and past him. Sammy was stranded mid-pitch as the fielder at point threw the ball to Lee, who broke the stumps to tie the game. Lee was never going to muck that up. Australia have held their nerve to pull this off
